17 fluorescent pink material as an outer garment and such material or garment is worn above
18 the waistline, and may include a head covering."
19 SECTION 2.
20 Said article is further amended by revising Code Section 27-3-25, relating to hunting bears
21 and required outer garments, as follows:
22 "27-3-25.
23 It shall be unlawful for any person to hunt bears or for any person to accompany another
24 person hunting bears unless each person shall wear a total of at least 500 square inches of
25 daylight fluorescent orange or fluorescent pink material as an outer garment during
26 firearms and primitive weapons seasons. Such clothing must be worn above the waistline
27 and may include a head covering."
28 SECTION 3.
29 Said article is further amended by revising Code Section 27-3-40, relating to hunting deer
30 and required clothing, as follows:
31 "27-3-40.
32 It shall be unlawful for any person to hunt deer or for any person to accompany another
33 person hunting deer during the firearms deer season unless each person shall wear a total
34 of at least 500 square inches of daylight fluorescent orange or fluorescent pink material as
35 an outer garment. Such clothing must be worn above the waistline and may include a head
36 covering."
37 SECTION 4.
38 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
